<classDescription><summary><![CDATA[<code>FlexApplication</code> is the default access point for Flex applications.]]></summary><restOfDescription><![CDATA[<p>Use this class to configure your application with Macromedia Flex. It inits
 your flex configuration in <a href="main_Flex.html">main.Flex</a> and your configuration for all 
 environments in <a href="main_Configuration.html">main.Configuration</a>.<p>You must simply init your application something like this:<pre>&#60;mx:Application xmlns:mx=<span class="codeString">"http://www.macromedia.com/2003/mxml"</span> initialize=<span class="codeString">"initApp();"</span>&#62;
  &#60;mx:Script&#62;
    &#60;![CDATA[
      <span class="codeKeyword">import</span> org.as2lib.app.conf.FlexApplication;
      <span class="codeKeyword">public</span> <span class="codeKeyword">function</span> initApp(<span class="codeIdentifier">Void</span>):<span class="codeIdentifier">Void</span> {
        FlexApplication.init();
      }
    ]]&#62;
  &#60;/mx:Script&#62;
&#60;/mx:Application&#62;</pre>]]></restOfDescription>
</classDescription>
